Taco Lindo is a hidden gem in Amsterdam! This cozy spot offers an authentic Mexican dining experience with a menu that's small but packed with flavor. Each taco feels like a trip to a different part of Mexico, featuring fresh ingredients and delicious homemade sauces that make every bite special. The Beef Birria and Cochinita Pibil are personal favorites--tender, perfectly seasoned, and incredibly satisfying. The option to add fresh onions, coriander, and lime for free gives it that extra touch of authenticity.

The atmosphere is relaxed and welcoming, with a small seating area that feels intimate yet vibrant. You can tell that quality is a priority here, as they focus on dine-in rather than delivery, ensuring that each dish is served fresh and hot. The staff are warm and knowledgeable, happy to answer questions or recommend a dish if you're unsure what to try.

If you're looking for real Mexican food in Amsterdam, Taco Lindo is the place to go! Great food, great vibe, and truly dedicated service. description: Tres amigos is family owned Mexican restuarant with fresh daily prepared food. You can buy foods such as big filled meal Burrito's, crunchy and juicy chicken and meat taco's or something simple as a quesadilla. All the meat we serve is Halal. Find us on Uber eats!

We went for the mezcal tasting collab with derrumbes. It was excellent. The mezcal was delicious and it was really interesting how different the different types tasted and paired with the food.

Speaking of the food this was as excellent as last time. Again we particularly enjoyed the tuna tostada with generous slices of very tasty tuna and the bbq dorade which was sizeable enough to make us need a few more tortilla s. I also really enjoyed the pumpkin quesadilla which we did not try before.

So in spite of the storm outside we had a fantastic dinner. We hope something similar will be organized soon and under better weather circumstances so more people can enjoy it!

Dinner was excellent. We are big fans of the original masmais so were very excited about visiting this fish focused sister restaurant. It did not dissapoint. As it s still the soft opening they work with a set menu so you can try a lot of the dishes. All of them were delicious. Bbqed dorade and tuna tostada s were stand outs.

In addition to the food the drinks and service are also great. We enjoyed the smokey paloma the most. Staff was attentive and (unneccessarily) apologized when one course took slightly longer.

The restaurant also looks really nice. The decor is warm and neat. Bar seats looked great as well. I couldnt figure out if these seats can be booked specifically (like at the sister restaurant) but we d definitely go for them if that was an option.

All in all highly recommend a visit. name: taqueria lima west
description:
Crazy good Mexican food. A whole lot of tacos, burritos, bowls and snacks, Taqueria LIMA has got it all!
Our chefs serve you the best classics like the taco Al Pastor, homemade braised beef or pulled chicken. But also a great Vegan Jack Fruit taco.
Come taste our light, fresh and easy going Mexican street food. El Super Taco Loco!

name: Madre
description: Ontdek Madre, het leukste Mexicaanse restaurant in Amsterdam! Geniet van modern Mexicaanse gerechten bereid met verse ingredienten, zoveel lokaal en biologische gesourced. Of je nu zin hebt in een gezellige avond in het restaurant of in lekkere drankjes in de cocktailbar,Madre biedt de perfecte sfeer. Goed nieuws: we zijn nu ook op maandag geopend! Madre is de ideale plek voor iedereen die op zoek is naar Mexicaans eten in Amsterdam. Reserveer snel en ervaar het leukste restaurant in de stad!

To the right there is a huge open kitchen  where you can watch the kitchen staff prepare your meal. Service was very good! Attentive, friendly but not annoying. Empty plates were removed almost instantly and we could order quickly aswell. The food was DELICIOUS! All veggie and vegan and the concept allows to share. We had the mushroom tacos which were super tasty, the cauliflower wings (also great) and (the cherry on top) roasted Yacon with mole sauce. The Yacon really surprised me! [{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQODlEd1dBEAE","rating":5,"name":"James Hickey","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112685893192889774800?hl=en-GB","review_text":"La Condesa Taqueria is a hidden gem! Tucked away down a small staircase (watch your head--it's a bit of a hobbit entrance), this unassuming spot delivers big on flavor. The decor is simple but charming, and the service is friendly and welcoming.

What truly stole the show were the tacos. I tried the vegetarian taco special: beer tempura-battered mushroom paired with a mix of fresh, flavorful ingredients. Absolutely delicious! Topped with the two sauces provided at the table, every bite was perfection. I could've easily ordered a second plate.

To end the meal, I had the tres leches dessert. While I've had slightly better versions elsewhere, this one was still delightful and perfectly enjoyable.

name: Rosario Cocina Mexicana
description:
Bij Rosario werken we met een kleine, regelmatig wisselende kaart, met gerechten uit de moderne Mexicaanse keuken, zoals we die zelf het liefste koken en eten.

At Rosario we work with a small, frequently changing, menu, with dishes from modern Mexican cuisine, the way we love to eat and cook it.

Our visit to Rosario was a truly great experience. We opted for the 6-course chef's menu and were taken on an exciting journey through the vibrant flavors of Mexican cuisine.

One of our party is a pescatarian, and the staff seamlessly accommodated her preferences without any issue, ensuring everyone could fully enjoy the meal.

The food was delicious, the drinks were spot-on, and the staff were incredibly friendly and attentive, which made the entire evening even more enjoyable.

One small detail to note: if you need to use the restroom, the hallway leading there is noticeably narrow. It's worth being aware of, but it didn't take away from our overall experience.

In short, it was a wonderful dining experience, and I'd definitely come again. Delicious modern Mexican food to enjoy by yourself or with friends/loved ones, nice drinks, good vibes, friendly and amazing personnel! I do recommend to make a reservation online just in case, just to make sure that you have a table reserved.

To start of I had the TACOS DE CAMARONES (2) with shrimp, chipotle crema topped with red cabbage and samphire. It was an flavour bomb!
So good! The balance of flavours was spot on!

After that I had the SERE DE PESCADO
Pan, a fried corvina in a red coconut sauce.
A Caribbean Mexican dish from the Garifuna community. It was soooo good!
The fish was perfectly cooked and the sauce just elevated the entire dish! The freshly baked bread that they also serve with the dish is great to scoop up all that tasty goodness off the plate.

For my 3rd meal I had the TACOS DE SUADERO (4), a Mexico City classic. Crispy fried beef brisket with a tomatillo salsa. It was tasty, and good hit of salt... although a bit oily (but that's just my personal opinion). The lime definitely helped to add some acidity to counter the saltiness and oily flavour.

To finish it off I had the caramel flan for dessert with a cappuccino + almond syrup on the side.
A nice and sweet way to finish off the food experience!

Would I recommend this place and come back in the future? [{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR2bDl1cDVRRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Urmi Dasgupta","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113733032294591759127?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Had a wonderful warm meal at this place during my first night in Amsterdam. A limited no thrills menu that focuses on flavor and affordability that serves corn tortillas. You cant even buy corn tortillas in the grocery stores in the Netherlands, so you know its fresh made here.
With the weekend specials being priced at 3euros per taco, this is the most affordable taco in Amsterdam, yet some of the best around. The only downside is that there is no mixing and matching tacos so you end up ordering a lot to try it all, or just come back another time if you dont want to stuff yourself.
If you want help deciding what to order, then pork carnitas are a good option, the veggie ones were great, but a bit saucy. I find in general, birria is a bit of an overhyped taco but I will say its good here. The chips and guacamole were Excellent and stood out.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzdG9yX3ZnRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Sarah Alexander","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109922017022792722055?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Loved my dinner at this place. Great service, excellent menu, tasty food, slightly uncomfortable seating, surprising ambiance and vibes.

Absolutely recommend trying the food here. They do a great job with the flavours, the meat, even their Mexican coffee!

I expected a expensive dining experience but somehow we were gooooood with a beer each while sharing 9 tacos between us 3. Which made it a very reasonably priced dinner! Desserts are good, the skull candy was such a fun surprise, but could skip if you have done justice to the main dishes :)

Overall, it's worth the hype! name: Maydanoz
description:
Ontdek de geheimen van de Turkse keuken.Smaken waar je blij van wordt.
Maydanoz is een mediterraan restaurant in Amsterdam waar de Turkse keuken centraal staat, met een menu dat zowel vleesliefhebbers als vegetariers en veganisten aanspreekt.
De gerechten worden bereid met de beste ingredienten en weerspiegelen de rijke diversiteit van de mediterrane keuken.
Van traditionele kebab tot verfijnde vegetarische schotels, bij Maydanoz is er voor elke smaakpapil wel iets te vinden. Uw nieuwe favoriete plek voor tapas in Amsterdam! Onze uitgebreide tapaskaart biedt een heerlijke mix van koude en warme hapjes, geinspireerd op de Turkse en Mediterrane keuken. Deel kleine gerechtjes met vrienden of familie en ontdek de veelzijdigheid van onze smaken.

name: Salsa Shop
description: Indulge in the rich, vibrant flavors of Mexico at the Salsa Shop Javastraat - your go-to Mexican quick service restaurant in Amsterdam. Conveniently located near you, this hotspot is the perfect destination for lunch or a delicious dinner. Whether it's a quick bite or a sit-down meal, Salsa Shop Javastraat offers a vast range of delicious Mexican food.

name: TAQUERIA LOCAL DEALER FOOD INC.
description:
Searching for an authentic Mexican restaurant Amsterdam? Local Dealer Food Inc. is a real family business serving up the true taste of Mexico!

Enjoy our mouthwatering tacos, zesty ceviches, refreshing margaritas, craft beers, and natural wines, all made with authentic flavors and a modern twist.

Join us every Saturday and Sunday from 12:00 to 16:00 for our lively Mexican brunch.  

Come experience the vibrant atmosphere and heartfelt, home-cooked flavor that only a family-run spot can offer!
Mexican Diner - Ceviches ~ Coctails~ Cervezas ~ Natural Wines

name: Los Pilones
description:
FROM MEXICO TO AMSTERDAM
From Mexico to Amsterdam
How it all came to be...

It all started in 2001 when Los Pilones opened the doors at Kerkstraat 63 and introduced authentic Mexican cuisine in The Netherlands!

Los Pilones is a Mexican cantina style concept, serving fresh home made food and drinks in a colourful and vibrant atmosphere - a fiesta straight from Mexico to Amsterdam. You can drop in for tacos, enchiladas, flautas, quesadillas, fresh margaritas, micheladas, over 200 different kinds of 100% agave tequilas and mezcal.

Pilon in Mexico means "a little extra" and that is exactly what we intend to give you when you visit Los Pilones!

name: Calle Ocho
description:
The best Miami streetfood restaurant land ate-night cocktailbar in the Pijp area in Amsterdam.

Calle Ocho: a warm, fun and buzzy ambience with some "gekkigheid". A place where you can take your tinder-date, grandmother or your volleyball team.

From Cuban to Mexican and from Caribbean to Tex-Mex. Calle Ocho is all of that in a nutshell. Our chefs translated this to a small menu which changes regularly.

name: Fiona
description:
Fiona, your go-to spot for Mexican cuisine in the heart of Warmoesstraat. Our menu is bursting with flavor, featuring all of your favorite dishes like tacos, nachos and quesadillas, as well as some of our own unique creations.

But it's not just the food that sets us apart - our atmosphere is just as vibrant and lively as the streets of Mexico. Our cozy and colorful interior, complete with traditional Mexican decor, will transport you south of the border.

So come on in, grab a seat, and let us take you on a culinary journey through Mexico. Whether you're in the mood for a quick bite or a full-on fiesta, Fiona has something for everyone. !Buen provecho!

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURmOGR1a2JBEAE","rating":3,"name":"Ellie Kenny","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111909726083246330877?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I am a little bit torn when writing this review. On one hand, the food and drinks were delicious. We opted for the taco Tuesday deal which was EU22 for one cocktail and two tacos. The cocktail was of high-quality and the tacos were very tasty. However, there were a few things which made this experience far from five stars. The price is quite high, I understand Amsterdam is quite expensive but even for Amsterdam I felt like the price was quite a lot. The food was good but the portions were quite small considering we spent almost EU50 on four tiny tacos. The interior design is very beautiful and cozy, however, we were seated against the wall  in what seemed like a waiting room with a tiny side table against the wall. When we arrived we were initially asked if we had a reservation and we said no, so we were told our choice was to sit at the bar or sit at the small tables. This is completely understandable as I understand places like this can be very busy so we were happy to sit at the small tables as we assumed it's very busy with lots of reservations. However, as time passed, we noticed that almost all of the tables and booths were empty with no one sitting in them so we wondered why we were told to sit in these uncomfortable small tables when there was an abundance of tables free. I assumed many people might not have turned up for their reservations but it felt a bit strange. A part of me wondered if it was because we weren't Dutch as there was a slight cold feel from the waiters that I couldn't shake off which really dampened the experience.","published_at":"6 days ago","published_at_date":"2025-01-07T18:07:08","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Ellie, 
Thank you for sharing your experience at Restaurant Fiona. 
We're sorry to hear that you felt the price-quality ratio didn't meet your expectations. We always strive to provide our guests with a great time, so it's disappointing to hear that we didn't meet your expectations this time.
We appreciate your feedback as it helps us to continuously improve and grow. Feel free to email us at info@fiona.restaurant if you'd like to discuss further details or if you have any other questions. We look forward to hearing from you!
Best regards,
Team Fiona

name: Alfonso's Mexican & Grill Restaurant
description:
In the beloved Utrechtsestraat in Amsterdam, located since 1986, you will find Alfonso's, an authentic Mexican restaurant. In a lively and friendly atmosphere you can enjoy the many famous specialties Mexico offers.
Several delicious fajitas, tacos burritos and tortillas adorn the menu.
Of course you can drink one of the cool Mexican beers or margaritas with the specialties on the table. You conclude your dinner with a tasty dessert or, for the real lover, a hearty coffee with a glass of tequila.

On my second visit to this establishment, I found that the ambiance and service continued to be fairly standard - nothing particularly noteworthy, but comfortable enough for a casual dining experience.

The highlight here is unquestionably the food, which stands a notch above the ordinary. We started with the Nachos Sonora, which, while bursting with flavor, fell short in portion size, especially as a dish advertised for two. The toppings, too, were on the scantier side, which was a bit of a letdown.

Moving on to the main course, the Combinacion Alfonso's was a mixed bag. The taco was average, failing to make much of an impression. However, the enchilada and burrito were a different story altogether - absolutely divine. These dishes alone make the restaurant worth visiting, elevating the overall culinary experience.

So, while it doesn't quite hit the five-star mark for me, it's definitely a solid choice for good food. We never had smaller arepas in our life and the patacones were sweet when patacones are supposed to be salty. Anyway we left hungry and for the price you don't expect to feel that way we payed 55 euros for mini arepas (see the pictures)","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-02T19:28:36","response_from_owner_text":"Hola Diana,
Thank you for sharing your feedback with us. We're glad you found our place appealing from the outside, but we're sorry to hear that your experience with the arepas and patacones did not meet your expectations.

When we processed your payment, we personally asked for your feedback and explained what had happened. It really helps us ensure you leave happy if you inform us right on the spot about any issues; we're always more than happy to make things right.

We have informed our kitchen about the size of the arepa, as they are typically larger, especially since they are meant to be bite-sized under our bites section on the menu. Thank you for your feedback; we will make sure the size of the arepa is always consistent moving forward. Unfortunately, you received a smaller size, but we could have addressed this immediately if you had let us know.

name: Mexicaans Cafe-Restaurant La Margarita Amsterdam
description: La Margarita. Het Mexicaans restaurant van Amsterdam! Al meer dan dertig jaar een begrip. Gevestigd in de Langebrugsteeg nr 6, het bruisend hart van Amsterdam. Tussen het Rokin en de Nes; op loopafstand van het Rembrandtplein en Dam, ontvangen wij u in een levendige en vriendelijke ambiance. Ons restaurant is geschikt voor een diner voor twee, maar ook voor bruiloften, recepties en groepen. Tot maximaal 98 personen kunt a la carte bestellen of, indien u dit wenst, kiezen voor een samengesteld menu.tevens zijn wij gespecialiseerd in glutenvrij eten

The upstairs area is nice but its a bit small, maybe only 20 people maximum can sit up there but there is a nice view of the canal.  We started off sitting downstairs until a table opened up upstairs.  The employees were really nice in accomodating us which was great.  Then we started off buying a pitcher of Mango margarita. Really tasty margarita.  We also started off with some nachos. It was interesting to see cucumber on nachos but the nachos taste was alright. name: Brouwerij Troost Westergas
description:
Brouwerij Troost Westergas is een brouwerij, brewpub en winkel ineen. In deze brouwerij worden de grote hoeveelheden geproduceerd van bieren als Pilsner, Extra Wit, I.P.A. en Honingblond. Jaarlijks brouwen en bottelen wij tot wel 700.000 liter! Ben je benieuwd hoe het werk tussen de ketels eruit ziet? Wij geven ook rondleidingen in onze prachtige brouwerij!
De brewpub is alle dagen open voor diner en in het weekend hebben we ook een heerlijke lunch. We hebben ook een aantal prachtige ruimtes voor groepen en partijen en je kan je eigen biertjes tappen met een muurtap!

description:
We're Cabron the Mexican Foodbar!

Located right at the Albert Cuyp Market we're bringing the rich and mouthwatering flavours of Latin America together. Come and join us for authentic food, proper tequila and fine craft beers at the cities most beloved hotspot!

name: Umami by Han Amsterdam
description:
Oriental Bar & Kitchen UMAMI by Han Amsterdam is a modern all-day concept where guests can choose for a quick lunch, lovely Asian finger-food or an extensive 3 course menu with 6 sharing-dishes per person.
The fresh ingredients, light dishes, wide variety of wines and tea-pairing are a great match with the health-consciousness of chef Han Ji.

name: Oliver Green
description:
Oliver Green is a plant-forward fast service restaurant. We serve healthy breakfast, (salad) bowls, smoothies and coffee.

All our food is made daily from scratch in our own kitchen from fresh ingredients delivered daily. We don't use added sugars, refined oils and have a whole food approach to our meals.

description: Welcome to SOIL Vegan Cafe - WEST, your go-to vegan restaurant in Amsterdam! We proudly serve a mouthwatering range of vegan comfort food designed to delight your taste buds. Whether you're looking for hearty meals or light bites, our menu has something for everyone. Enhance your dining experience by pairing your meal with our carefully selected artisanal beers and natural wines. Our cafe features a warm and inviting atmosphere that welcomes all. If you're hunting for a vegan-friendly spot in Amsterdam, look no further--SOIL is the perfect place to indulge in vibrant, plant-based cuisine!

We ordered 3 starters/sharing bites and 2 mains, all together; however, they were not served all at the same time as it seems that the kitchen is a little slow. We also had to re-order one item that got forgotten.

name: Restaurant Cancun Amsterdam
description:
At Cancun Amsterdam, we blend the vibrant spirit of Latin culture with the rich flavors of Mexican and Caribbean cuisine to create a unique dining and entertainment experience.
From tantalizing dishes prepared with fresh, authentic ingredients to dynamic events featuring the best in salsa, bachata, and Latin music, we're dedicated to bringing the essence of Cancun to Amsterdam.
Join us for a journey of taste, rhythm, and unforgettable moments.

Where Flavors and Rhythms Meet.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR2ci1TSy1nRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Andrei Basa","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100829136588925293664?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Foodhallen is the perfect place for food lovers! I had the most delicious bitterballen there--crispy on the outside and incredibly tasty on the inside. Paired with some amazing Dutch beers, it was the ultimate treat. The vibrant atmosphere, enhanced by a DJ playing great music, made the experience even more enjoyable.

What really stood out was the attentive and respectful staff, who made sure everything was just right. There's also an incredible variety of food options to choose from, catering to all tastes. Whether you're a fan of street food, local dishes, or international flavors, Foodhallen has something for everyone.

Let me break down my thoughts for you.

First up, I tried the Mexico City dish, which consists of eggs served over a tortilla. Honestly, it was just okay. I appreciate the attempt to bring a taste of Mexico to the menu, but it felt a bit underwhelming. If you're aiming for a true Mexican breakfast vibe, I'd suggest they switch it up and serve the over easy eggs over red chilaquiles instead. Chilaquiles are essentially tortilla chips smothered in salsa and topped with eggs, cheese, and sometimes chicken or beans. Trust me, everyone would love it. The Mexico City dish has some of the right elements, but it's not quite there yet.

Now, let's talk about the French toast. Oh. My. God. It was made with brioche, and it was absolutely amazing. The brioche gave it this wonderfully soft and fluffy texture that just soaked up all the syrup and butter perfectly. It was sweet, decadent, and exactly what you want from a French toast. I would come back just for this dish alone.

The coffee was also top-notch. Sometimes, brunch places can slack off on the coffee, but not here. It was rich, flavorful, and just the pick-me-up I needed. Whether you're a coffee aficionado or just need your morning caffeine fix, you won't be disappointed.

A big shoutout to the staff as well. They were kind, smiley, and really made the experience enjoyable. Good service can make all the difference, and the team at The Breakfast Club definitely knows how to treat their customers right.

All in all, I'd say "The Breakfast Club" is definitely worth a visit. They've got some fantastic dishes on the menu and a great atmosphere. Even though the Mexico City dish needs some tweaking, the French toast and coffee more than make up for it. Plus, with such a friendly staff, you're guaranteed a pleasant time. I'll definitely be coming back to try more of their offerings. If you're looking for a new brunch spot, give The Breakfast Club a shot!","published_at":"6 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-07-05T15:22:07","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Ismael! name: Taco Mundo Amsterdam Oud-Zuid
description: Maak de Mexicaan in je los en bestel de lekkerste Mexicaanse gerechten eenvoudig bij Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Oud Zuid. Je kunt kiezen uit onder andere onze befaamde Tacos, Rijkgevulde Burritos, heerlijke Quesadillas en natuurlijk onze beroemde Nachos. Als afsluiter kun je kiezen uit onze verrassende Taco Mundo Ice Creams of bijvoorbeeld onze onweerstaanbare Churros. Wat je ook kiest... Je tovert met een druk op de knop jouw avond om in een Mexican FIESTA!

name: iBoenda
description:
Ontdek de authentieke smaak van Indonesie bij iBoenda. Met liefde bereid door een Indonesische moeder, bieden wij verse, huisgemaakte maaltijden vol rijke, traditionele smaken. Laat je verrassen door onze uitgebreide cateringopties en afhaalmaaltijden die de echte Indonesische keuken naar je tafel brengen. Proef de passie, proef de liefde!
Discover the authentic taste of Indonesia at iBoenda. Lovingly prepared by an Indonesian mother, we offer fresh, homemade meals full of rich, traditional flavors. Be surprised by our extensive catering options and takeaway dishes that bring the true Indonesian cuisine to your table. Taste the passion, taste the love!

First up, I tried the Gado-Gado, a delightful mix of veggies with peanut sauce. The dish included cabbage, green beans, and eggs, all topped with a rich and thick peanut sauce that provided a wonderful peanut flavor. The vegetables were perfectly boiled, adding a satisfying texture to the dish.
Next, I sampled the Nasi Campur, a traditional Indonesian dish. This platter had an assortment of items including rendang and vegetables. The rendang, one of Indonesia's national dishes, was absolutely delicious. Its rich and complex flavors complemented the fried rice perfectly.
Overall, Iboenda impressed me with its authentic flavors and high-quality ingredients. If you're in Amsterdam and craving Indonesian cuisine, I highly recommend giving Iboenda a try. It is little paradise in my opinion! You will never get an authentic, traditional and fantastic home cooked cuisine anywhere in the world as good as this restaurant! I've eaten in Indonesia too...I'm not exaggerating. They also do take aways and an equivalent to 'Just Eat'. I ate in the restaurant twice it was that good. I just wanted to try a little bit of everything. It's like a buffet style counter where you can choose whatever you like, honestly it's amazing and the restaurant is clean. I am only in Amsterdam for a few days but I guarantee, I will be visiting iBoenda a second and hopefully a third time again before I leave. I hope my mum won't ever get to read this as she doesn't use the internet, but as much as I love her Indonesian cooking, this Indonesian restaurant is far better and that is saying something, because I love my mum's cooking. If you miss Indonesian food, or whether you have never tried it, I absolutely recommend you eat in and get a take away too as you will not be disappointed with the food and price. Seriously, my mouth is watering just thinking about it! Thank you to the lady on the train that recommended this restaurant/take away. name: Senor Mostachio
description:
Welcome to Senor Mostachio, we pride in serving authentic Mexican cuisine in a relaxed and sophisticated setting in the heart of Amsterdam. Celebrate everything that is wonderful about Mexican cuisine by experiencing Senor Mostachio mexican cantina.

Senor Mostachio offers an impressive array of traditional Mexican dishes sure to please even the most discriminating palate. Indulging on home-made tortilla chips and fresh salsa or traditional tacos. Carefully prepared which compliments any meal. At Senor Mostachio we offer an amazing assortment of imported beers, cocktails, and margaritas! Perfect place for groups!

Upon browsing uber eats, little inspiration came until, like a flash from the holy lord, Tomatillo stood before us like el Salvador. My wife ordered just the burrito with pico de gallo and raved about it. I added habanero sauce on the side with mine and had it in a bowl. It came with two corn tortillas to make my own tacos with it. It was super good.

name: Oaxaca Amsterdam
description: An ancient gastronomic heritage. Eating at OAXACA is like being transported to Mexico. Through ancestral techniques, planting a multitude of Mexican produces in our gardens and "milpas", and cooking with native ingredients. We're talking about nixtamalized corn dough ground on volcanic stone. Knowledge of all the chiles, "soasados" and "tatemados", charcoal-grilled fish, pre-Hispanic "moles" and stews. Guacamole prepared in a "molcajete" and spicy sauces, just as they are made and enjoyed in Mexico.

name: Tabeya Expat Shop Amsterdam
description: Tabeya is an international expat delicatessen which reflects the owners love for home food as well as food discovered during work and travels all over the world. Find foods you miss from home and if you can't find it with us, please let us know and we will strive to get in for you if we can. We have a wide selection of British, Irish, American Mexican, Caribbean, South African, Asian, Africa, Vegetarian, Gluten Free, Baking, Organic, Vegan, Frozen, Chilled, Locally Sourced, Seasonal and more. Teas, Pies, Crumpets Ciders, Beers, Ales Cereals, Soups, Cadburys, Cheetos, Oreos, McVities, Kraft etc.

As a junk food fanatic, it's rare to find great food here in the Netherlands, and burgers in particular are trending as everyone's business now, that even falafel trucks (if there were any) would be selling burgers!

As a first timer, I usually order restaurant specials, today I got:

1) Monopoly beef burger.
Not a tomato in your burger kinda guy here, but I didn't mind it at all in this sandwich, the bun was heavenly, the patty was exquisitely cooked, the balance of meat-to-seasoning was immaculate, and although it doesn't drip a lot, but the way each bite smoothly melts in your mouth is worth it all.

2) Monopoly hotdog:
Processed cheese aka cheddar/American isn't my thing, but as it was stuffed into the hotdog, with delivery time, it still kept warm, again the hotdog bun was out of this world; the sandwich was simple, neat, and can easily be eaten anyway one holds their hotdog sandwich!

3) The Nachos Locos:
Where they use waffle fries instead of chips, and I was on my toes to try this one as I don't like variations of fries; wedges, waffle, or pomme swirls, but this was excellent, crunchy on the outside, so darn fluffy on the inside.
However, I didn't really care for the monopoly sauce that comes with it, as for me it was under seasoned, and can easily be lost in the crowd.

Packaging was very neat, I loved it a lot, it's like they do pay attention to the littlest details when it comes to their orders.

What I'd like to see improved is:
1) Monopoly sauce, seasoning and flavours are a tad bland, being their signature sauce; it needs some work.

2) Fries to box/toppings ratio in the nachos locos, I ran out of waffle fries so fast, had to get a spoon and dig into the what may seem like heaps of toppings that comes with.

Overall, I'll definitely keep ordering from them, and cannot wait to try their other menu items.

name: Bar Lempicka
description: Bar Lempicka is een stijlvolle bar - brasserie in het hart van Amsterdam, met een zonovergoten terras aan de Amstel. Drink een cocktail of een van de vele speciaal bieren aan de indrukwekkende bar binnen of neem front-row buiten plaats om lekker mensen en bootjes te kijken. Bij Bar Lempicka kun je elke dag van vroeg tot laat het leven vieren met mediterrane shared dining gerechtjes. Door de unieke locatie op de hoek Sarphatistraat/Amstel, op een steenworp afstand van theater Carre en de Hermitage, is Bar Lempicka de ideale uitvalsbasis voor theater- of museumbezoek.

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNSak5QZUhREAE","rating":5,"name":"Charbel Aoun","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101074965378028524227?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Review of Manoto Restaurant, Amsterdam

Manoto Restaurant in Amsterdam is a true gem, offering an unforgettable dining experience that perfectly blends exceptional food, warm hospitality, and a cozy ambiance. My visit to this restaurant was nothing short of delightful, and I left thoroughly impressed.

The menu is a celebration of Persian cuisine, with a wide variety of dishes that are both authentic and flavorful. Each dish was beautifully presented and bursting with rich, aromatic flavors that showcased the skill and dedication of the chefs. The kebabs were grilled to perfection, tender and juicy, while the saffron-infused rice was a highlight, adding a fragrant and colorful touch to the meal.

What truly stood out to me was the quality of the ingredients. Everything tasted fresh, and it was evident that great care had gone into selecting and preparing each component. The portions were generous, offering excellent value for money.

The atmosphere at Manoto was another highlight. The restaurant exudes a welcoming charm, with tasteful decor that reflects the Persian heritage while maintaining a modern and inviting vibe. Whether you're visiting for a romantic dinner or a meal with friends and family, the setting is perfect.

The staff were friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu, offering helpful recommendations and ensuring that every aspect of our dining experience was enjoyable. Their genuine warmth added a personal touch that made the visit even more memorable.

Manoto also offers a well-curated drinks menu, with both traditional Persian beverages and a selection of wines and cocktails to complement the meal. The saffron tea, in particular, was a perfect way to round off the evening.

In conclusion, Manoto Restaurant is a must-visit for anyone in Amsterdam looking to explore Persian cuisine or simply enjoy a high-quality dining experience. name: Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Nieuw West
description: Maak de Mexicaan in je los en bestel de lekkerste Mexicaanse gerechten eenvoudig bij Taco Mundo Amsterdam-Nieuw West. Je kunt kiezen uit onder andere onze befaamde Tacos, Rijkgevulde Burritos, heerlijke Quesadillas en natuurlijk onze beroemde Nachos. Als afsluiter kun je kiezen uit onze verrassende Taco Mundo Ice Creams of bijvoorbeeld onze onweerstaanbare Churros. Wat je ook kiest... Je tovert met een druk op de knop jouw avond om in een Mexican FIESTA!

name: Larry's
description: Discover Larry's, your go-to sandwich shop in Amsterdam for tasty, quick service steamed buns Whether you're looking for lunch near you or seeking the best fresh quality buns in Amsterdam, Larry's is the spot. From our popular Duk bao bun to an array of vegan-friendly options, we cater to every palate. Our restaurant is well-known for its diverse menu, providing you with flavors from around the globe. Larry's is not just another fast-food restaurant near you; we provide you with pillowy steamed buns loaded with mouth-watering fresh flavors from all over the world. Buy at your own health risk! As a response to their reply: best by date is not communicated at all on their website, and yes, I received a partial refund for half of the products past due, whilst I asked for a return and full refund of all these products. Does not seem right to me, but make your own choice when you want to buy products here.","published_at":"9 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-04-04T16:23:59","response_from_owner_text":"Beste Wim,
 
U heeft bij ons producten gekocht uit de Outlet/Sale categorie.
We begrijpen dat er enige verwarring kan zijn rondom de houdbaarheidsdatum van de producten die u heeft gekocht. We willen benadrukken dat we ons best doen om deze informatie zo transparant mogelijk te communiceren. Alle producten op onze website worden duidelijk gepresenteerd met hun houdbaarheidsdatum, en we vragen bij elke toevoeging aan uw winkelwagen uw akkoord met deze datum. Daarnaast wordt de houdbaarheidsinformatie nogmaals vermeld in uw winkelwagen, tijdens het afrekenproces en op de factuur die u ontvangt. Desondanks begrijpen we dat het voor sommigen nog steeds niet volledig duidelijk is, en we zullen intern bekijken hoe we dit nog duidelijker kunnen verwoorden.

Ons doel is om ervoor te zorgen dat al onze klanten volledig op de hoogte zijn van de houdbaarheidsstatus van de producten die ze bij ons kopen, terwijl we tegelijkertijd streven naar het tegengaan van voedselverspilling door producten met een beperkte of verlopen houdbaarheidsdatum tegen gereduceerde prijzen aan te bieden. De uiteindelijke beslissing om deze producten al dan niet aan te schaffen ligt altijd bij de klant. 

Ondanks ons eerdere klantcontact om tot een oplossing te komen, hebben wij als gebaar van goodwill de kosten van de producten teruggestort op uw rekening. Het is teleurstellend om te horen dat u nog steeds niet tevreden bent en dat u zich zo voelt. We willen graag dat al onze klanten een positieve ervaring hebben met onze service, en we betreuren het dat we niet aan uw verwachtingen hebben kunnen voldoen.
","response_from_owner_ago":"9 months ago","response_from_owner_date":"2024-04-05T13:05:07","review_likes_count":2,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":"Dear Wim,
 
You have purchased products from us from the Outlet/Sale category.
We understand that there may be some confusion surrounding the expiration date of the products you have purchased. We would like to emphasize that we do our best to communicate this information as transparently as possible. All products on our website are clearly presented with their best before date, and we request your agreement to this date with each addition to your shopping cart. In addition, the shelf life information is mentioned again in your shopping cart, during the checkout process and on the invoice you receive. Nevertheless, we understand that it is still not completely clear to some, and we will look internally at how we can express this even more clearly.

Our aim is to ensure that all our customers are fully aware of the shelf life status of the products they purchase from us, whilst at the same time aiming to reduce food waste by offering products with a limited or expired shelf life at reduced prices offer. The final decision whether or not to purchase these products always rests with the customer. 

Despite our previous customer contact to find a solution, we have refunded the costs of the products to your account as a gesture of goodwill. It is disappointing to hear that you are still not satisfied and that you feel this way. We want all our customers to have a positive experience with our service, and we regret that we were unable to meet your expectations.

Injera is a traditional Ethiopian fermented spong bread made of teff flour, gluten-free, dairy free, and rich in protein. Its texture is between a pancake and a crepe.

name: The Uptown Meat Club
description: Wij zijn The Uptown Meat Club. Premium vlees restaurant in Amsterdam nabij het Vondelpark. Bij ons geniet je van de beste steaks; van rib-eye tot dry aged cote de boeuf. Gerechten als de Tomahawk XXL lenen zich uitstekend voor shared dining. Op het menu staan tevens ook vegetarische-, glutenvrije en kindvriendelijke opties. We hopen je snel te verwelkomen voor lunch of diner in ons premium steak restaurant Amsterdam.

Unfortunately, the experience didn't meet our expectations, starting with the service.

When I requested my steak to be cooked medium, there seemed to be some miscommunication. Although the doneness levels were explained on the menu, it took a while for the waitress to understand, and I had to point it out. This interaction felt a bit awkward, and I suspect there might have been a language barrier.

As for the food, it was disappointing. My steak, which I ordered medium, arrived well-done and lacked flavor. My partner and I had specifically chosen this restaurant hoping for a higher-quality dining experience, but we regretted not opting for a more reliable option.

The wine selection added to the frustration. We initially chose a wine made from three different grape varieties listed on the menu. However, it wasn't available, and the suggested alternative was described as "similar." When we asked about the grape varieties in the new option, we couldn't get a clear answer. Upon checking the label ourselves, we realized it was a completely different wine with only two grapes. This lack of attention to detail was disappointing.

Overall, the experience fell short in both service and food quality. The restaurant has a great atmosphere, but it was understaffed, leading to significant delays. Despite prior communication, we weren't informed we'd be seated downstairs in front of the kitchen, where we spent the evening surrounded by cooking smells. Service issues included delays in drinks, an overcooked main dish, and a need to correct the order for two non-pork eaters. The bathroom was also not clean.

name: SLA
description: Sla de bekendste saladebar van nederland. Bij Sla kan je terecht voor lunch, salade en voor lunch Amsterdam. Voor salades, lunchen, afhalen en ben je op zoek naar een vegetarisch restaurant. We zijn vegan restaurant, vegetarian restaurant maar hebben ook gezonde salade met biologische kip. Dus op zoek naar lunch near me? Sla's veggie Caesar salade, een spicy vegan Tofurama, een middle feast met homemade falafel of een Killer Kapsalon met vegan shoarma. Je vindt het bij Sla the good food saladebar voor eten afhalen, lunches, vegetarisch eten en vegan food. Maar Sla is niet alleen restaurant vegetarisch. Een van de fijnste lunch restaurants in amsterdam, een gezond vegetarisch restaurant amsterdam, afhaalrestaurant. Kom voor je afhaal salade.

name: De Burgerfabriek
description:
You can find us in one of the most international known neighbourhoods of Amsterdam, "The red light district", an area full of history and controversy, which has been changing rapidly the last years, evolving into an eclectic mixture of local flavours and foreign cultures, where past and tradition meet future and avant-garde.

The concept of Burgerfabriek is a combination of old essence in a contemporary suit.

We come back to basics: fresh, fast, flavourful food pimped with a modern twist. An industrial and rough, but cushy space; and a kitchen based on organic, primary, quality ingredients, with a touch of sophistication

Burgerfabriek features also comfortable tables where you can tap your own beer.
Come Enjoy the Burgerfabriek experience
